<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                        <gloss type="to">German Emperor</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Mansion</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-12"><hi rend="italic">August 12, 1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>I am gratified to receive Your Majesty’s message of goodwill in
                                relation to the selection of Count Waldersee, and, like you, I see
                                in our common duty an additional recognition of the kindly ties and
                                mutual interests that exist between this country and Germany.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">William
                                McKinley.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>